By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Federal Capital Territory Administration (FCTA) on Saturday confirmed twelve new cases of COVID-19. The FCTA in a post shared on its Twitter handle confirmed that the total number of active cases remains at 56. The tweet read: “TWELVE (12) NEW CASES IN THE FCT. “Summary of #COVID19FCT as at 10:40pm, 18th April, 2020; Total number of confirmed cases: 81 “Total number of active cases: 56, Total discharged: 23, Deaths recorded: 2 “Residents are urged to continue to stay home and stay safe.” Meanwhile, NCDC on Saturday recorded forty-nine confirmed Coronavirus cases. This brings the total number of confirmed cases in the country to 542. ABUJA - Four patients receiving treatment for coronavirus in Abuja have been discharged after recovering from the disease. The federal capital territory administration (FCTA) announced this in a tweet on Saturday. “The FCTA has confirmed the discharge of four (4) #COVID19 patients, bringing the total number of discharged to eleven… April 11, 2020 In "Top Stories" •NCDC Director-General, Dr. Chile Ihekweazu ABUJA - The number of confirmed cases of the novel coronavirus (COVID-19) in Nigeria has risen to 36, one addition to the 35 initially announced on Monday morning by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC). The figure rose after the Nigeria Centre for Disease… March 23, 2020 In "News" ABUJA - A total of eight new cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been recorded in the country, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has confirmed. In a tweet on Sunday evening, the health agency says the new infections bring the total number of confirmed cases in Nigeria to 232.… April 5, 2020 In "Top Stories"